author: @TheManWhoCanBeMovedd
text:
I just recently got into kpop 3 or 4 months ago. I never thought I’d be a kpop fan as I never liked it before.

I’ve heard many kpop songs before (Blackpink, RV, etc) but I’m still not a kpop fan. It didn’t feel special.  AND THEN…..
Few months ago, I heard Twice’s what is love. I liked the song and searched which girl group performed it. 
I got addicted to that song and after a few days of listening to it, I got curious about Twice and A NEW ONCE WAS BORN.

Twice made me love kpop girl groups ( i don’t listen to boy groups, pls don’t hate me) for me, twice pulled me into kpop. I started appreciating blackpink, red velvet, itzy, and many more. 

My girlfriend even got annoyed because she’s not my wallpaper anymore. It’s Momo! HAHA

I realized I stopped listening to AirSupply, BeeGees, etc (I’m not old. I just loved old songs)

Twice transformed me. I became a Simp. LMAO ILOVEYOU MOMO

I STAN TWICE. MOMORING IS MY BIAS.

I am saving money so that I can watch Twice’s concert by selling my paintings. I hope they’ll comeback to PH. WOOOOO

text:
I'll be frank here tho. The reason why Momo is considered as the best dancer in the industry is because she does explore every genre of dancing and also I do really get reminded of by someone and yeah it's Hyoyeon of Girls Generation. Hyo even said tho that Momo really is a great dancer and that being said is no longer debatable. The similarity I'm seeing between Hyo and Momo they really do explore all genres of dance, contemporary R&B pop jazz bass edm Musical dramatic hiphop ballad rock all types of genre. So if you're going to compare and bring up Lisa here please do fact checking first. Lisa only sticks to one genre or two to three, Jazz R&B and pop. Momo just like what I said on the top can do different genre's in dancing. Momo can also pull off the ballroom dance though to be honest if only she was given enough freedom by the company. But anyways, Stream SCIENTIST and THE FEELS MV.

Edit: SCIENTIST MV is now on its way to hit 100M views. The Feels just hit 200M views last week y'all, keep on streaming.

author: @kaisendbd
text: 🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢 NUNCA había visto algo con tal esfuerzo de ser racista y de hacer apropiación cultural (de forma incorrecta). Primero, el vestido de Momo es de tango, algo realmente SINSENTIDO considerando que el título del vídeo es "Momo's margarita dance" así que debió USAR UN VESTIDO DE MÉXICO ya que la bebida Margarita es de México, no de ARGENTINA Y URUGUAY, de dónde es el tango. A Jyp no le importa si hace las cosas de forma correcta. A Jyp no le importa conocer la historia de los países latinos. No le importa si está siendo racista y haciendo apropiación cultural (de manera incorrecta) sin saber de dónde es la margarita.  También mencionar que jyp está tratando de dar a entender que "margarita, mojito y piña colada" son palabras en inglés cuando no lo son. Esta canción debería ser eliminada debido a ser tan ofensivamente asquerosa para los países latinos debido a ser tan incorrecto sobre de dónde es cada bebida y el vestido. Esto está más allá de ser asqueroso y la gente no debería aceptar esta broma enfermiza. También mencionar que en jyp no les importa para nada Latinoamérica que ni siquiera escribieron bien "margarita" en el título. 🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢

author: @kaisendbd
text:
🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢

I never seen something with the effort of being that RACIST and doing cultural appropiation. First, the dress that momo's using is to dance tango which is FROM ARGENTINA AND URUGUAY, which is a BIG NONSENSE when we see the title of the video that is "Momos MARGARITA dance" And as we all know the MARGARITA DRINK IS FROM MEXICO, NOT ARGENTINA OR URUGUAY. JYP DOESNT CARE ABOUT BEING CORRECT, DOESNT CARE ABOUT KNOWING THE ACTUAL STORY FROM LATIN AMERICA COUNTRIES, DOESNT CARE IF HES BEING RACIST AND DOING CULTURAL APPROPIATION WITHOUT KNOWING WHERE MARGARITA DRINK IS FROM. This is beyond disgusting and sickening. I don't know why people doesnt care ABOUT this. Jyp also is trying to imply that "Margarita, mojito and piña colada" are English words when they arent. This song should be removed due to being this wrong and not being made correct. 🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢🤢
